      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in pristine condition. This specimen features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six engine, characterized by its individual throttle bodies and high-pressure Double VANOS variable valve timing system. This vehicle has undergone comprehensive preventive maintenance, including a documented rod bearing replacement and a structural subframe reinforcement\u2014critical for the chassis longevity of this platform. The 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox offers tactile, short-throw engagement, routing power through a variable M-differential lock. The exterior retains its factory depth and clarity, while the interior showcases impeccable Nappa leather with no evidence of bolster compression or wear. Every bushing, gasket, and mechanical tolerance remains within factory specification, ensuring the razor-sharp handling and 8,000 RPM symphonics the M-division intended.",
